19
00:00:18,439 --> 00:00:19,857
<i>Turning the tide!</i>

20
00:00:19,941 --> 00:00:23,694
<i>As Separatist control over vital
but isolated supply routes expands,</i>

21
00:00:23,778 --> 00:00:28,115
<i>Republic forces invade a key planet,
the darkened world of Um bar a.</i>

22
00:00:28,282 --> 00:00:30,826
<i>In the midst of helping
Obi-Wan Kenobi's battalion</i>

23
00:00:30,910 --> 00:00:32,370
<i>conquer the Um bar an capital,</i>

24
00:00:32,453 --> 00:00:35,206
<i>Anakin Skywalker
is called away to Coruscant.</i>

25
00:00:35,289 --> 00:00:37,124
<i>His battalion is temporarily placed</i>

26
00:00:37,166 --> 00:00:39,752
<i>under the command
of Jedi General Pong Krell,</i>

27
00:00:39,961 --> 00:00:42,296
<i>a shrewd and temperamental leader.</i>

28
00:00:42,838 --> 00:00:44,298
<i>Krell's reckless strategy</i>

29
00:00:44,340 --> 00:00:48,844
<i>forced Captain Rex to retreat
with his platoons in a disastrous defeat.</i>

30
00:01:11,284 --> 00:01:13,578
We have got to move
before those fighters come back.

31
00:01:13,661 --> 00:01:16,205
Rex! Rex, over here!

32
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:21,877
Jesse, take the right flank.
Dogma, take the left flank.

33
00:01:31,178 --> 00:01:33,681
It'll be okay, buddy. This will ease the pain.

34
00:01:43,524 --> 00:01:45,443
<i>The capital city's too fortified.</i>

35
00:01:45,526 --> 00:01:47,445
<i>We need your battalion to help us take it.</i>

36
00:01:47,903 --> 00:01:51,115
Resistance from the Umbarans
has been greater than anticipated.

37
00:01:51,198 --> 00:01:52,700
We're holding our ground at the moment.

38
00:01:52,908 --> 00:01:55,328
<i>We've gathered intel
on an airbase to the west.</i>

39
00:01:55,369 --> 00:01:57,038
<i>It is re-supplying the capital's defenses.</i>

40
00:01:57,079 --> 00:01:58,205
Incoming ! Incoming!

41
00:01:58,956 --> 00:02:00,625
Get down, get down!

42
00:02:03,044 --> 00:02:06,422
<i>If you could capture that airbase,
it will sever the capital's supply lines</i>

43
00:02:06,631 --> 00:02:08,758
<i>allowing the rest of our forces to move in.</i>

44
00:02:09,091 --> 00:02:12,219
I'll see to it that the airbase
is placed under our control.

45
00:02:12,637 --> 00:02:13,846
<i>Remember, General Krell,</i>

46
00:02:13,888 --> 00:02:17,767
<i>the entire invasion
depends on your battalion.</i>

47
00:02:18,392 --> 00:02:21,020
Captain Rex,
have those coordinates mapped

48
00:02:21,103 --> 00:02:23,356
and all troops ready
to move out immediately!

49
00:02:23,397 --> 00:02:24,565
Yes, General!

50
00:02:49,173 --> 00:02:52,176
There's a base there, all right,
and it's heavily guarded.

51
00:02:53,094 --> 00:02:55,346
At least three tank divisions, plus guns.

52
00:02:55,763 --> 00:02:57,973
We'll advance along the central gorge

53
00:02:58,057 --> 00:03:01,602
and engage their forces
in a full-forward assault.

54
00:03:01,644 --> 00:03:03,270
The gorge is narrow, sir.

55
00:03:03,437 --> 00:03:06,524
We'll only be able to move our platoons
in single squads.

56
00:03:07,149 --> 00:03:10,361
Perhaps a closer recon will tell us
if there's a more secure route.

57
00:03:11,112 --> 00:03:14,407
Obi-Wan and the other battalions
are holding off the enemy right now

58
00:03:14,615 --> 00:03:16,742
while they wait for us to take out this base.

59
00:03:17,118 --> 00:03:19,787
We don't have time
to look for a more secure route.

60
00:03:21,372 --> 00:03:22,540
Yes, sir.

61
00:03:33,968 --> 00:03:35,636
All right, listen up.

62
00:03:35,678 --> 00:03:37,805
We'll assemble the squads
into two divisions.

63
00:03:37,930 --> 00:03:40,975
We'll move straight up this gorge
towards the airbase at the far side.

64
00:03:41,392 --> 00:03:43,144
The casualties are going to be high.

65
00:03:43,269 --> 00:03:44,979
Is Krell trying to get us killed?

66
00:03:45,146 --> 00:03:48,023
You know, I wasn't sure
that Krell was crazy before,

67
00:03:48,107 --> 00:03:50,109
but now I'm positive.

68
00:03:50,401 --> 00:03:51,986
We had to retreat from the capital

69
00:03:52,069 --> 00:03:55,322
because the General pushed
a flawed strategy. Now this?

70
00:03:55,656 --> 00:03:57,783
I don't know! Could be fun.

71
00:03:57,867 --> 00:04:00,494
Well, I, for one,
agree with the General's plan.

72
00:04:00,703 --> 00:04:03,497
We're running out of time
and this is the best option.

73
00:04:03,789 --> 00:04:08,210
No recon? No air support?
We don't know what we're up against.

74
00:04:08,627 --> 00:04:10,921
They have weapons
we've never seen before.

75
00:04:11,255 --> 00:04:14,425
A few of General Skywalker's plans
seemed reckless, too,

76
00:04:14,675 --> 00:04:15,760
but they worked.

77
00:04:15,843 --> 00:04:20,014
Yeah, but General Skywalker is usually
leading his men up in the front

78
00:04:20,264 --> 00:04:22,683
not bringing up the rear like General Krell.

79
00:04:23,017 --> 00:04:26,020
A full-forward assault
would leave us too exposed.

80
00:04:30,691 --> 00:04:31,692
We have to look at other options.

81
00:04:31,776 --> 00:04:33,944
-It's going to be a meat grinder.
-Fives.

82
00:04:38,866 --> 00:04:41,368
It would help if you eased their minds.

83
00:04:41,827 --> 00:04:45,206
What, you mean coax them into following
another one of Krell's suicide missions?

84
00:04:45,331 --> 00:04:46,957
We lost a lot of men last time.

85
00:04:47,166 --> 00:04:50,836
Krell may do things differently,
but he is effective in getting them done.

86
00:04:51,253 --> 00:04:52,671
He's a recognized war hero.

87
00:04:53,088 --> 00:04:56,717
He may have had some victories,
but have you seen his casualty numbers?

88
00:04:56,759 --> 00:04:59,970
More troopers have been killed
under his command than anyone else!

89
00:05:00,763 --> 00:05:02,223
That's the price of war, Fives.

90
00:05:03,307 --> 00:05:06,018
We're soldiers.
We have a duty to follow orders and,

91
00:05:06,060 --> 00:05:09,146
if we must, lay down our lives for victory.

92
00:05:09,814 --> 00:05:11,440
You believe that,

93
00:05:11,524 --> 00:05:14,068
or is that what you were
engineered to think?

94
00:05:14,109 --> 00:05:17,404
I honor my code. That's what I believe.

95
00:05:28,791 --> 00:05:32,086
-Is everyone clear on the plan? Hard case?
-Yes, sir.

96
00:05:32,127 --> 00:05:35,756
-Fives, are you clear?
-Yeah.

97
00:05:35,965 --> 00:05:38,759
All right, get in your groups.
Let's move out.

98
00:06:07,788 --> 00:06:10,666
Everybody stay alert.
Fingers on the trigger.

99
00:06:14,712 --> 00:06:16,630
They look spooked.

100
00:06:18,507 --> 00:06:19,884
What the...

101
00:06:27,349 --> 00:06:29,268
Oh, skrag!

102
00:06:34,481 --> 00:06:35,482
Blast it!

103
00:06:56,795 --> 00:06:57,963
Look out!

104
00:07:00,174 --> 00:07:01,926
Its head is ray-shielded!

105
00:07:02,009 --> 00:07:03,844
We need rocket launchers!

106
00:07:15,022 --> 00:07:18,150
Mayday, mayday!
Rex, we need rocket launchers now!

107
00:07:20,694 --> 00:07:23,322
Get those rocket launchers down there!
Move it, troopers!

108
00:07:31,372 --> 00:07:33,540
-Take it, take it.
-Thanks, buddy.

109
00:07:33,624 --> 00:07:35,876
I got him, I got him.

110
00:07:38,128 --> 00:07:39,546
Go! Go, go, go!

111
00:07:40,297 --> 00:07:41,674
Keep moving, keep moving!

112
00:08:09,118 --> 00:08:11,745
-That was close.
-You got a point there.

113
00:08:11,912 --> 00:08:13,539
Move it, trooper.

114
00:08:16,375 --> 00:08:18,585
Everyone regroup, now! Take cover!

115
00:08:19,003 --> 00:08:20,462
Move it! Move it!

116
00:08:28,012 --> 00:08:30,931
We're safe for the moment,
but they'll be coming around any second.

117
00:08:31,390 --> 00:08:34,601
Bring up the launchers,
spread detonators along that corridor.

118
00:08:34,768 --> 00:08:38,188
Trap them into the bottleneck.
We're going to blow those things sky high.

119
00:08:40,816 --> 00:08:42,609
Hurry up, we only have a few seconds.

120
00:08:49,491 --> 00:08:50,617
Here they come!

121
00:08:53,245 --> 00:08:54,621
Hey, come on ! Over here!

122
00:08:54,663 --> 00:08:55,956
-Let's see how tough you are!
-Hey! Hey! Hey!

123
00:08:55,998 --> 00:08:57,291
Right over here!

124
00:08:57,666 --> 00:08:58,792
Over here!

125
00:09:19,354 --> 00:09:21,315
We got her! We got them!

126
00:09:22,483 --> 00:09:24,902
Good job! All right, let's move out.

127
00:09:51,386 --> 00:09:53,764
That one's still got some juice in it,
waste it!

128
00:09:53,847 --> 00:09:54,848
Sure.

129
00:10:01,855 --> 00:10:03,357
No juice left in him either.

130
00:10:08,362 --> 00:10:10,989
Hey! Still hungry?

131
00:10:11,448 --> 00:10:12,658
Chew on that!

132
00:10:16,078 --> 00:10:17,996
Everyone, keep moving.

133
00:10:19,248 --> 00:10:20,624
Hey, Kix, leave it.

134
00:10:43,230 --> 00:10:44,439
We've got a problem.

135
00:10:47,651 --> 00:10:50,112
Fall back! Fall back now!

136
00:11:06,545 --> 00:11:08,297
What are they doing?

137
00:11:08,672 --> 00:11:10,757
Captain, continue your attack!

138
00:11:10,841 --> 00:11:14,136
Sir, we're overpowered.
We need reinforcements!

139
00:11:14,553 --> 00:11:17,556
The rest of the battalion is holding
the entrance to the gorge, Captain.

140
00:11:17,639 --> 00:11:20,684
They're guarding it so your troops
can break through to the airbase.

141
00:11:23,103 --> 00:11:25,606
-Sir, we can't possibly...
-You must stand your ground!

142
00:11:25,647 --> 00:11:26,773
Do you read me?

143
00:11:26,940 --> 00:11:28,942
<i>Captain, are you listening?</i>

144
00:11:29,109 --> 00:11:31,862
Do not fall back! That is an order!

145
00:11:36,033 --> 00:11:38,452
The platoons are in the formation
you requested, General.

146
00:11:38,827 --> 00:11:40,704
Should I send them
to support Captain Rex?

147
00:11:41,121 --> 00:11:44,458
I'll give the order when I give it,
Sergeant Appo.

148
00:11:56,220 --> 00:11:58,055
Keep the wounded as quiet as possible.

149
00:11:58,305 --> 00:12:00,974
All right, you heard the General. Let's go.

150
00:12:01,016 --> 00:12:02,809
You can't be serious.

151
00:12:02,976 --> 00:12:05,229
I used to think General Krell was reckless,

152
00:12:05,312 --> 00:12:07,522
but now I'm beginning to think
he just hates clones.

153
00:12:07,606 --> 00:12:10,192
The Captain is right. Now let's move out.

154
00:12:11,151 --> 00:12:14,571
We can't take them head-on.
We need to find another way.

155
00:12:14,780 --> 00:12:16,406
You got any ideas?

156
00:12:18,450 --> 00:12:19,743
Then this is it.

157
00:12:21,286 --> 00:12:23,622
Okay. Let's do it!

158
00:13:05,580 --> 00:13:07,791
The rocket launchers
don't work on these things!

159
00:13:20,762 --> 00:13:23,056
Help me with the wounded!

160
00:13:25,892 --> 00:13:28,061
We got to get these guys out of here.

161
00:13:36,111 --> 00:13:37,738
Forget it, we have to leave them!

162
00:13:38,071 --> 00:13:39,239
We can't just leave them, sir!

163
00:13:39,323 --> 00:13:41,450
You don't have a choice. That's an order!

164
00:13:41,742 --> 00:13:43,577
You sound like General Krell.

165
00:13:45,495 --> 00:13:48,623
Look, Kix, it's more important
to save yourself right now.

166
00:13:48,874 --> 00:13:51,460
If we survive,
you can patch up the wounded later.

167
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:55,714
We're finished.

168
00:13:55,756 --> 00:14:00,302
We've still got some fight left in us, Tup,
and I've got an idea.

169
00:14:01,053 --> 00:14:02,137
What were you thinking?

170
00:14:02,346 --> 00:14:03,472
Remember what you were saying

171
00:14:03,555 --> 00:14:06,016
about finding another way
to destroy those tanks?

172
00:14:06,099 --> 00:14:09,394
-Yeah.
-Well, I have a mission for you.

173
00:14:10,228 --> 00:14:12,939
CT-7567, where are you?

174
00:14:13,190 --> 00:14:16,735
<i>General Krell, we've come up with a plan
to infiltrate the airbase.</i>

175
00:14:16,777 --> 00:14:18,278
What is your plan?

176
00:14:18,487 --> 00:14:21,698
<i>I've dispatched two men
on a stealth incursion into the airbase.</i>

177
00:14:21,782 --> 00:14:25,327
<i>They've been ordered to co-opt star fighters
and use them against the tanks.</i>

178
00:14:25,494 --> 00:14:26,745
You what?

179
00:14:26,787 --> 00:14:29,664
You've put this entire assault on your hope

180
00:14:29,748 --> 00:14:33,210
that two clones can do
what your entire group could not?

181
00:14:33,752 --> 00:14:36,129
<i>Sir, the rocket launchers
don't work on these tanks</i>

182
00:14:36,380 --> 00:14:38,340
<i>and it'll be easier to slip by undetected</i>

183
00:14:38,423 --> 00:14:40,467
<i>while the rest of us
keep the tanks occupied.</i>

184
00:14:40,634 --> 00:14:43,970
Captain, you will launch
a full-forward strike immediately

185
00:14:44,012 --> 00:14:46,515
or you will be relieved of duty.

186
00:14:48,809 --> 00:14:50,644
We need to hold out as long as we can.

187
00:14:50,852 --> 00:14:54,189
I'm trusting Fives and Hard case
to pull this thing off.

188
00:14:54,898 --> 00:14:57,317
The second they spot us, I start blasting.

189
00:14:57,734 --> 00:14:59,986
Hard case, can't you take it easy for once?

190
00:15:00,195 --> 00:15:02,906
Stick to the plan, instead of guns blazing.

191
00:15:03,198 --> 00:15:05,033
I'm sorry, it's just how I am.

192
00:15:05,158 --> 00:15:08,495
My commander on Kamino said my
growth acceleration chamber had a leak.

193
00:15:08,787 --> 00:15:10,622
Made me hyper-active, I guess.

194
00:15:10,664 --> 00:15:12,249
Shh ! There's the airbase.

195
00:15:19,047 --> 00:15:20,048
Hmm...

196
00:15:22,008 --> 00:15:23,468
Some kind of sensor wall.

197
00:15:28,682 --> 00:15:30,350
Use the tree to get over the sensor wall.

198
00:15:31,017 --> 00:15:34,688
Uh, how am I supposed to do this, exactly?

199
00:15:35,313 --> 00:15:36,314
Figure it out.

200
00:15:43,029 --> 00:15:46,032
"Figure it out, Hard case. Figure it out."

201
00:15:46,158 --> 00:15:47,951
What's to figure out
about climbing up a tree?

202
00:15:48,034 --> 00:15:49,744
How about you try it next time?

203
00:15:53,039 --> 00:15:54,624
Great, nice view.

204
00:16:00,172 --> 00:16:02,549
I prefer a good fight
to all this sneaking around.

205
00:16:35,999 --> 00:16:38,960
Wow, I never actually thought
that would work.

206
00:17:47,028 --> 00:17:49,155
So, how do I start this thing?

207
00:17:49,322 --> 00:17:51,866
Well, how should I know?
Start pushing buttons!

208
00:18:11,011 --> 00:18:12,512
Glad these things are ray-shielded.

209
00:18:27,485 --> 00:18:29,446
I don't think I can do this!

210
00:18:35,577 --> 00:18:36,828
Watch out!

211
00:18:54,888 --> 00:18:56,806
Let's hope this trip was worth it.

212
00:18:57,015 --> 00:18:58,308
All right, let's go!

213
00:19:07,233 --> 00:19:09,903
Hey, Kix, put it down, you're wasting aim.

214
00:19:29,923 --> 00:19:32,801
-Clear out, Captain !
-The big guns have arrived, sir!

215
00:19:48,692 --> 00:19:49,901
Take that!

216
00:20:01,454 --> 00:20:02,622
That's the stuff!

217
00:20:08,294 --> 00:20:09,963
Whoo-hoo!

218
00:20:10,797 --> 00:20:12,465
Way to go, boys!

219
00:20:13,341 --> 00:20:14,759
Attaboy, Hard case!

220
00:20:17,220 --> 00:20:18,638
All right, let's bring them home.

221
00:20:24,102 --> 00:20:25,353
Impressive.

222
00:20:25,895 --> 00:20:28,314
Sergeant, their defenses are down.

223
00:20:28,398 --> 00:20:31,776
Send in the rest of our forces.
Attack the airbase!

224
00:20:32,068 --> 00:20:33,862
All units, move out.

225
00:21:04,392 --> 00:21:07,937
Despite Hardcase's flying,
you two saved us all.

226
00:21:08,313 --> 00:21:09,564
That wasn't so tough.

227
00:21:09,856 --> 00:21:13,151
You sure? You looked a little green
when you came out of that fighter.

228
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:17,405
Captain. Report. What is our situation?

229
00:21:19,282 --> 00:21:23,036
General, we have taken the base and
cut off enemy supply lines to the capital.

230
00:21:23,536 --> 00:21:28,792
Luck has smiled on you today, Captain.
Consider yourself fortunate.

231
00:21:29,292 --> 00:21:33,546
It wasn't all luck, sir.
A lot of men died to take this base.

232
00:21:33,838 --> 00:21:38,218
The price for such victory.
Perhaps someday you'll realize this.

233
00:21:44,265 --> 00:21:45,600
Dismissed.

234
00:21:47,310 --> 00:21:50,146
He's the one who will never realize.

235
00:21:50,170 --> 00:21:55,170
http://hiqve.com/

